---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Max Digital Garden and the idea behind this blog.">
  <section class="container about-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>A place for thoughts with roots and version history.</h1>
  </section>
  <section class="prose about-copy">
    <p>
      Max Digital Garden is meant to be a personal blog: a home for essays,
      project notes, technical experiments, and everything that does not fit
      into a quick social media post.
    </p>
    <p>
      The content deliberately lives as Markdown in the GitHub repository. That keeps
      everything versioned, portable, and simple enough to understand years from now.
    </p>
    <p>
      Decap CMS adds a comfortable writing interface, so new entries can also happen
      on the go without opening a code editor.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    padding: 80px 0 34px;
  }

  h1 {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0;
    font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 8vw, 6rem);
    font-weight: 520;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .about-copy {
    padding-bottom: 84px;
  }
</style>
